See README for dependecies.

If you get code from VCS, you will need Autotools (automake, autoconf,
libtool) in addition and you must prepare build system with `autoreconf
--install'.

Then run `./configure && make && make install' to build and install library
into your system.

If you want to change installation directory use appropriate configure
argument (see `./configure --help' for more details).

If you want build example clients, add `--enable-example' to configure. You
can run and study example clients in `client' subdirectory.

If you want build and run library internal tests, add `--enable-test' to
configure. You can run tests by `make check'. You can run and study each test
in `test' subdirectory.

Example clients and tests are not installed by `make install'.
